                <p className="mb-4 leading-relaxed">
                  Players begin with nothing, foraging food, crafting basic tools, and learning
                  the medieval world&apos;s systems through exploration. Survival mechanics govern
                  hunger, temperature, and health, but Bellwright distinguishes itself from
                  pure survival games by layering <strong>settlement construction</strong> as the
                  core long-term progression system. Players designate building sites, assign
                  followers to construction tasks, and develop their camp into a full village
                  with production chains spanning farming, woodcutting, smithing, textile work,
                  and food processing.
                </p>
                <p className="mb-4 leading-relaxed">
